      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", read ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "עְמות עְשֵׂרִים",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", will make good Hebrew syntax, and be in harmony with the Septuagint (Alexandrian), and with the Syriac and Arabic Versions. This gives the height of the porch as 20 cubits, which will be in harmony with the general height of the building, which was 30 cubits. Thus far, then, the plan of the temple is plain. The house is 60 cubits long, ",
        "children": []
      },
